-->

- `<default-slide>`
- `md`-only

We can put basically anything we want
into the `slide.note` field.

<!-- @slide
webc: |
  <h3>Put WebC in here…</h3>
  <oddbird-logo style="fill: deepPink"></oddbird-logo>
-->

- `<default-slide>`
- `webc`-only

<!-- @slide
todo: |
  - finish building this
  - ship it
caption: a `todo` slide
-->

ToDo slides accept arbitrary markdown.
These are mostly provided as a placeholder
while writing a talk,
but could also be used to talk about
things that need to get done!

